						###########################################################################
						#|||||||||||| User Space Thread Library|||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||#
						###########################################################################
						
						---------------------------------------------------------------------------
						|							Compiling and Linking						  |
						---------------------------------------------------------------------------
						
						1) Compile with 
						
								gcc -w FreakThread.c FreakTimeLogger.c FTLTestApplication.c -o finalout
								gcc -w -m32 FreakThread.c FreakTimeLogger.c FTLTestApplication.c -o finalout								
							
								
						2) Next to see that the threads are only created in the user space and are not visible. 		
						   at the kernel level run following command to see the process tree .You will get the 
						   process id of the current process at the starting.
						   In other terminal execute following
						
								watch -n 1 pstree -h <process ID>							
						

						###########################################################################
